Amazing night with two #washingtonlegends @bayoubullet @garyclarkinc. Hundreds of fans across the DMV came to hear stories about Doug and Gary’s experiences, and what it took to build a championship legacy on and off the field. To see their Legacy live on in the DMV community 40 years later was special. Hearing the stories of families who can remember where they were when Doug led @commanders to a Super Bowl win as the first black Qb to win a Super Bowl in @nfl history was lifechanging . True Legends on and off the field. 
.
.
Whether you played one season or 20 for the burgundy and gold, hit me up. Spread the word. We’re building a best in class organization which supports former players and connects our legacy to the current team, fans and community. Great time to be a part of the burgundy and gold family! 
#sustainablechampionshipculture
